Description: Corroded iron small and thin chisel or wedge, with rectangular cross-section, slightly convex sides tapering to a cutting edge at one end and with a flattened head at the other.
Curator's comments: One of the "chisels (pl. xxxviii. 15 to 20), of which about forty were kept, beside many rejected", mentioned by Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 78 § 78, p. 110, pl. xxxviii, 20.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 78 § 78, p. 110, pl. xxxviii, 20)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.47, p.75, p.184, pl.26)
